duration: Duration of the call in seconds
number: Identifier for the caller/callee (depends on type).  > 0 values represent users from the study and match the user_id column, values < 0 represent devices outside the study.
timestamp: Unix-time of the sample in milliseconds
type: Type of the call event: 1 - incoming call, 2 - outgoing call, 3 - missed call.
user: Unique identifier for each user. Note: it is an id, not a counter for users. Numbers higher than 850 doesn't mean there are more users
